name: HeapPriorityQueue
comment:
Heap based priority queue.

The elements are kept in a heap structure, where the element with the highest priority is immediately accessible, and modifying a single element takes logarithmic time in the number of elements on average.

  • The collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.add and collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.removeFirst operations take amortized logarithmic time, O(log(n)), but may occasionally take linear time when growing the capacity of the heap.

  • The collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.addAll operation works as doing repeated collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.add operations.
  • The collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.first getter takes constant time, O(1).
  • The collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.clear and collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.removeAll methods also take constant time, O(1).

  • The collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.contains and collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.remove operations may need to search the entire queue for the elements, taking O(n) time.

  • The collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.toList operation effectively sorts the elements, taking O(n*log(n)) time.

  • The collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.toSet operation effectively adds each element to the new set, taking an expected O(n*log(n)) time.

comparison.name: comparison
comparison.comment: The comparison being used to compare the priority of elements.

first.name: first
first.comment:
Returns the next element that will be returned by collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.removeFirst.

The element is not removed from the queue.

The queue must not be empty when this method is called.

constructors.comment:
Create a new priority queue.

The collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.HeapPriorityQueue-.comparison is a dart-core.Comparator used to compare the priority of elements. An element that compares as less than another element has a higher priority.

If collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.HeapPriorityQueue-.comparison is omitted, it defaults to collection/dart-core.Comparable.compare.

add.name: add
add.comment:
Adds element to the queue.

The element will become the next to be removed by collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.removeFirst when all elements with higher priority have been removed.

clear.name: clear
clear.comment: Removes all the elements from this queue.

contains.name: contains
contains.comment:
Checks if collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.contains.object is in the queue.

Returns true if the element is found.

remove.name: remove
remove.comment:
Removes an element that compares equal to collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.remove.element in the queue.

Returns true if an element is found and removed, and false if no equal element is found.

removeAll.name: removeAll
removeAll.comment:
Removes all the elements from this queue and returns them.

The returned iterable has no specified order.

removeFirst.name: removeFirst
removeFirst.comment:
Removes and returns the element with the highest priority.

Repeatedly calling this method, without adding element in between, is guaranteed to return elements in non-decreasing order as, specified by collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.comparison.

The queue must not be empty when this method is called.

toList.name: toList
toList.comment:
Returns a list of the elements of this queue in priority order.

The queue is not modified.

The order is the order that the elements would be in if they were removed from this queue using collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.removeFirst.

toSet.name: toSet
toSet.comment:
Return a comparator based set using the comparator of this queue.

The queue is not modified.

The returned dart-core.Set is currently a collection/dart-collection.SplayTreeSet, but this may change as other ordered sets are implemented.

The set contains all the elements of this queue. If an element occurs more than once in the queue, the set will contain it only once.

toString.comment:
Returns some representation of the queue.

The format isn't significant, and may change in the future.

hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of collection/dart-pkg-collection.HeapPriorityQueue.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.
